<paragraph blockId="3.[151,704,945,1008]" box="[151,415,981,1008]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,323,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1767,1792]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,189,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,179,1739]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–24. Habitus (dorsal view and lateral view), crown, pronotum and scutellum (dorsal view), and face. 1–4, Takagioma pagoda sp. nov.; 5–8, Takagioma rostra sp. nov.; 9–12, Takagioma gladius sp. nov.; 13–16, Takagioma curvata sp. nov.; 17–20, Takagioma anguis sp. nov.; 21–24, Takagioma longicauda sp. nov" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677809/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Figures 13–16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[336,407,981,1008]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–56" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1679,1704]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,188,1643]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1653]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 50–56. Takagioma curvata sp. nov. 50, genital capsule, ventral view; 51, pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; 52, subgenital plate, ventral view; 53, subgenital plate, lateral view; 54, paramere, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view; 55, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; 56, abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677817/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">50–56</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1053,1692]" box="[151,769,1053,1080]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,323,1054,1080]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Measurement.</emphasis>
Male, 3.67–3.93mm (including wings).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1053,1692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1089,1116]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Description.</emphasis>
Body ochraceous with whitish stripe thin on vertex; eyes gray; pronotum, scutum and scutellum yellowish, pronotum with triangular brown patch centrally. Face brown with apical margin ochraceous. Forewing yellowish in basal 4/5, with irregularly brownish smoky patch on apical cell, hind wing with CuA branched.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1053,1692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">
Abdominal apodeme reaching 4th abdominal sternite (
<figureCitation box="[811,888,1197,1224]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–56" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1679,1704]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,188,1643]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1653]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 50–56. Takagioma curvata sp. nov. 50, genital capsule, ventral view; 51, pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; 52, subgenital plate, ventral view; 53, subgenital plate, lateral view; 54, paramere, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view; 55, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; 56, abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677817/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Fig.56</figureCitation>
). Pygofer hook short and strongly curved laterad (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,1233,1260]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–56" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1679,1704]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,188,1643]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1653]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 50–56. Takagioma curvata sp. nov. 50, genital capsule, ventral view; 51, pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; 52, subgenital plate, ventral view; 53, subgenital plate, lateral view; 54, paramere, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view; 55, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; 56, abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677817/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate broad at base with apical 1/3 widen and folded dorsad, with 4 macrosetae and some rigid microsetae laterally near base and numerous microsetae apically and laterally on folded part (
<figureCitation box="[1183,1311,1269,1296]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–56" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1679,1704]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,188,1643]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1653]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 50–56. Takagioma curvata sp. nov. 50, genital capsule, ventral view; 51, pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; 52, subgenital plate, ventral view; 53, subgenital plate, lateral view; 54, paramere, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view; 55, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; 56, abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677817/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Figs 52, 53</figureCitation>
). Paramere long and gradually narrowing distally with both ends nearly equal length, central part expanded (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1322,1305,1332]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–56" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1679,1704]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,188,1643]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1653]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 50–56. Takagioma curvata sp. nov. 50, genital capsule, ventral view; 51, pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; 52, subgenital plate, ventral view; 53, subgenital plate, lateral view; 54, paramere, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view; 55, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; 56, abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677817/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
). Connective with central lobe developed and extended beyond lateral feet. Aedeagal shaft slender and straight; dorsoatrium straight in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[417,548,1377,1404]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–56" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1679,1704]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,188,1643]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1653]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 50–56. Takagioma curvata sp. nov. 50, genital capsule, ventral view; 51, pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; 52, subgenital plate, ventral view; 53, subgenital plate, lateral view; 54, paramere, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view; 55, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; 56, abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677817/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Figs 54, 55</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
