<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1053,1692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1522,1548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Notes.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Qin &amp; Kang &amp; Huang &amp; Zhang, 2020" authorityName="Qin &amp; Kang &amp; Huang &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2020" box="[612,824,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Takagioma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladius" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis box="[612,824,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Takagioma gladius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[832,917,1522,1548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[832,917,1522,1548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302" rank="species">sp. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in body coloration and the shape of aedeagus, but can be distinguished by the curved pygofer hook, centrally widened paramere and the narrow base of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
