<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="302" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1053,1692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1630,1656]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from Latin adjective “ 
<emphasis box="[942,1038,1630,1655]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">curvatus</emphasis>
”, which means “curved”, referring to the strongly curved pygofer hook.
</paragraph>
